        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p>The <persName>bearer </persName><persName>Mr. John Little of <placeName>Westmoreland County</placeName> in the 
Commonwealth of Pennsylvania</persName> about to remove down the <placeName>River </placeName>to the
<placeName>Province of Texas</placeName> wishes a certificate of his Character etc</p>

<p>I the subscriber do hereby certify that I have known said <persName>John
Little</persName> for more than twenty years and know him to be an, honest,
sober, orderly Citizen   <date when="1822-04-06">April 6th 1822</date></p>

<p><persName>Andrew Boggs </persName>   [Rubric]</p>
<p><placeName>Pennsylvania</placeName></p>

<p><placeName>Allegheny County</placeName></p>

<p>I <persName>James K. Butler Prothonotary of the Courts</persName> of Common pleas
in and for the <placeName>County of Allegheny</placeName>, in the <placeName>Commonwealth of 
Pennsylvania</placeName> Do hereby Certify that I am intimately acquainted with
<persName>Andrw Boggs</persName>, who has in his own proper handwriting given the
above certificate and subscribed his name thereto, That he is a man
of strict truth and integrity, to all whose certificates and acts faith
and credit are due.</p>

<p>In Testimony whereof I have hereunto set my hand and affixed the
seal of the said <placeName>Court at Pittsburgh</placeName> this <date when="1822-04-10">tenth day of April in the year
of our lord Eighteen hundred twenty two</date> - and of the sovereignty
and Independence of the <placeName>United States of America</placeName>, the forty sixth.</p>

<p><persName>James R. Butler.</persName> <hi rend="italic">Prothy</hi></p>

        </div1>
